Actress Sandra Bullock has given one million dollars to the American Red Cross to boost its tsunami relief campaign, the organisation said Monday. ``Sandra continues to enable our lifesaving work and is a model for personal generosity,'' said Marsha J. Evans, the American Red Cross president. Among the stars who will take part are : Avril Lavigne, Sarah McLachlan, Sum 41 and the Barenaked Ladies. Canadian record label Nettwerk Management has enlisted some of its big guns to perform in benefit concerts at the end of the month. 